---
import "../styles/global.css";
import Nav from "../components/Nav";
import EventDetailPanel from "../components/EventDetailPanel";
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <title>About — Events Ledger</title>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;500&family=Playfair+Display:wght@400;500&display=swap" rel="stylesheet" />
  </head>
  <body class="bg-white min-h-screen">
    <Nav current="/about" client:load />
    <main class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-4 pt-20 pb-24 md:pb-8">
      <p class="font-serif text-2xl text-neutral-900 mt-4 mb-8">About</p>
      <div class="space-y-5 text-sm text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          Events Ledger is my personal archive of live performances I've attended. Think theatre, ballet, opera, circus, comedy, magic, classical music, cabaret, gigs, drag, and whatever else I could talk myself into.
        </p>
        <p>
          The data is patchy, which is entirely past Claire's fault. Past Claire had a very loose definition of record-keeping. She wrote "fringe show" in her calendar like that would mean something later. She let other people buy the tickets and then had no idea what she'd paid. She went to things spontaneously and then just… didn't write them down. Some things lived on paper, some in her head, some were lost completely because she trusted future Claire to remember and future Claire did not.
        </p>
        <p>
          So, recent years are well-documented, but anything before 2025 is reconstructed from patchy calendar entries, email confirmations, and asking my mum/friends. Prices are sometimes estimates. Casts are sometimes incomplete. And dates are sometimes approximate.
        </p>
        <p>
          But now it will become a place to memorialise all the great events I see, a place to write my small takes, take-downs or post a link to a full length essay. A ledger of performance artistry.
        </p>
      </div>
    </main>
    <EventDetailPanel client:load />
  </body>
</html>
